Conda documentation:

In cdac: source source Conda/bin/activate
cd swayamshree/
ls
Conda env list (To see the existing environments)
conda create -n amber (To create an environment as amber)
conda activate amber (To activate any environment)
conda install python=3.6 numpy=1.17.2 (To install any version of package)
conda remove -n amber â€“all (To remove the environment)
conda deactivate (To deactivate conda environment)


If we have environment.yml file for some package, we can use that to create the environment with the specified packages in that environment.yml file:
conda env create -f environment.yml

